OL,7,FCalls for his resignation have been
OL,8,Fmounting since his guilty plea, and
OL,9,Fthere has been growing frustration
OL,10,Fthat there has been no mechanism to
OL,11,Fremove him from his job before his
OL,12,Fsentencing in January.
OL,14,FChief Minister Deputy Lindsay de
OL,15,FSausmarez lead those calls and said
OL,16,Fthe law surrounding politicians'
OL,17,Femployment in general will be reviewed.
OL,19,FShe said: "The Reform Law is not an
OL,20,Feasy law to change,"
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/7
