OL,7,FShe clarified that while standard
OL,8,Fvetting procedures would most likely
OL,9,Fnot have flagged anything in regards
OL,10,Fto Le Tocq's case, better processes
OL,11,Fwould "enable the public to have more
OL,12,Fconfidence in the people standing for
OL,13,Felection".
OL,15,F"It is a position in which people put
OL,16,Fconsiderable trust in those
OL,17,Findividuals, and I think it is right
OL,18,Fthat we can have more confidence in
OL,19,Fthose who stand for election and are
OL,20,Fsubsequently elected.
